Task 3: Build Kibana Dashboards
Step 1: Create Index Pattern
Access Kibana at http://localhost:5601
Navigate to Management > Stack Management > Index Patterns
Click Create index pattern
Enter: user-behavior-*
Select @timestamp as time field
Click Create
Step 2: Create Visualizations
Risk Score Distribution (Bar Chart):

Go to Visualize Library > Create visualization
Select Vertical Bar
Y-axis: Count
X-axis: Terms aggregation on risk_score
Save as "Risk Score Distribution"
Top Risky Users (Data Table):

Create Data Table visualization
Metrics: Sum of risk_score
Buckets: Terms on user.keyword, order by metric descending
Save as "Top Risky Users"
Activity Timeline (Line Chart):

Create Line visualization
Y-axis: Count
X-axis: Date Histogram on @timestamp
Save as "Activity Timeline"
Activity Type Breakdown (Pie Chart):

Create Pie visualization
Slice by: Terms on activity_type.keyword
Save as "Activity Types"
Step 3: Build Dashboard
Go to Dashboard > Create dashboard
Click Add and select all visualizations
Arrange visualizations logically
Set time range to Last 1 hour
Enable Auto-refresh (10 seconds)
Save as "User Behavior Risk Monitoring"
